ust went on with the bathing and washing of the - you know, the broken heads and whatnot that had happened. Wonderful in her way, you see, wonderful in her way, really. But - a strange - very strange household. And now - no relief you see, the no poor rel
i
ef. You see there was no poor relief - no - nothing - you couldn't turn to anything in those days for - for any relief you see and it - it was wonderful how she coped with it all - coped with it all - without - without any charity at all. There was no - n
o - she - well in fact I don't suppose she would ever have accepted it. And I never remember her turning a beggar away from the door in my life. And poor as we were if anybody }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5603085\charrsid11536143 knocked}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143  on the door - and there was plenty of beggars in those days - she would a
lways offer them either a cup of tea - a pot of tea and a piece of bread or if we had no tea she - she'd give them water. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5603085\charrsid11536143 Brutal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143  - never, never turned anybody away. And if she had a penny she would give it to them and - very, very, - she used to say oh wel
l never mind I might be in need myself sometime and - well, you see, I didn't tell you about my birth. This was - this was what I learned years after. The father had got a job in Ashton-under-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5603085\charrsid11536143 Lyme}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143  and he'd written to the family and - in glowing terms. They
 were foolish enough to decide to follow him. Oh he said he'd got a house for them. So they were foolish enough to follow him. And - they went to this house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Ashton-under-Lyne{\*\xmlclose}
 - it didn't last long because they were unknown to the people who kept the sho
ps - they wouldn't let them have any credit - oh he got - he got pitched out as usual - he must have had a row or something - and he was out of work. Well, nobody would help them - the poor law said they hadn't been resident in the town long enough, you s
ee, you had to have a residential qualification. The shopkeepers didn't know them and wouldn't lend them any strap - you know what strap is don't you? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5603085\charrsid11536143 
So the result was that they decided they'd have a moonlight flit, you see, the arrears of rent had run on 
