r
ought the altar boy to stand as sponsor for the birth you see. So I was even born in tragic circumstances. Yes. So you - but she never - she never referred to it once in the whole of her life but it was my sister that told me that - a few years before she
 died. And I thought, well, we were a tragic group. But - but I don't remember father ever facing up - you know - to the responsibilities - as a parent - in fact I don't think he ought ever to have been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13978893 
Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 . He would have been much better as a bachelor. Plodding his own - going his own way you see. Un-untrammeled by either wife or family.
