No, it was the elder girl, as I say, Kathy. She was the little mother. We - we had a very simple rite of going to bed when I was a child I mean. We would undress downstairs and put on our nightdress - the two of u
s went to bed together, Emily and I, you see - and my sister would generally wash us, wash our face and hands before I went to bed, comb our hair and then we'd just knelt down and said our prayers and that was - that was always insisted on - we knelt down
 
said our prayers and then we just stood on the staircase - it was a little round staircase like that that went up from the kitchen and we had a drink of water - nothing to eat - and went off to bed you see. But it was always Kathy - nearly always Kathy wh
o it did that. If Kathy wasn't in of course mother would do it, but it was a very simple going to bed - there was no fuss or that you see and we used to lie awake telling each other stories until of course we fell asleep you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012655 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 Did you have to go at a certain time?
