Oh well, I think it was on during the war. They were pioneers in that, you see, and I know I went once or twice to look at the school and they had a - a very nice person in ch
arge of the - some of the girls, teaching them cooking and shopping and what foods to buy and all that kind of thing. They also had English and the - they had arithmetic and they had a very, very fine amateur dramatic society, you see, made up of most of 
these young - young people that went in and they had quite a lot of outdoor recreation - tennis and bowls for the men and football and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568115\charrsid11536143 clubrooms}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
