Fairly early - fairly early, yes. Before ever Courtaulds came in. Courtaulds is the best now for their schemes because they have three pension schemes. 
One is absolutely free - the operatives don't pay anything at all. There's another one that they pay a proportion and then there's another one that they can join so that quite a lot of them have a very, very good pension when they leave - very good indeed
. And they have, of course, very, very good - welfare facilities. But not - there weren't many of them in those days - they were the pioneers. They were the pioneers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012655 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 Did they have these schemes before the war ended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14835199 AF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 Oh yes, I should think - prob
ably not as well developed as they were between - probably twenty and thirty - 1920's and 1930's - because you see, there was a terrible slump in cotton after the war because, you see, we'd lost most of the markets, you see, by not being able to get the r
aw cotton to England, you see, all the - the boats were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13568115\charrsid11536143 being}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 
 sunk, you know, you remember that time. Well, you won't remember, you're much younger - but the Germans of course were sinking most of the cargo boats coming across so that we got no raw cotton t
he result was we lost most of the markets that we'd previously had, you see. So after the war there was a short fierce boom 'til about 1922 and then there was a col - oh a colossal slump which lasted into the thirties you see. And so these schemes for wel
f
are and that kind - and pensions - well, they were just nowhere and it was only after the revival - after the nineteen thirties and leading up to the second world war that - they were taken up again you see, being able to spend money on them. Then of cour
