e, you see, during the war we got provision, you see, for compulsory - for canteens, canteens had to be provided you see, where there were so many work people so that - it - it almost came all these things in a rush - kind of a - a rush period you see. Th
e
y've become now accepted. Nobody would ever dream, you see, of - of saying you mustn't have canteens but - they can't do without them now because of the shift system because you see, you've no time to go home to meals where there's only half an hour for t
