\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012655 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 Would this be a sort of humanitarian equivalent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14835199 AF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 Yes.
 I should think that in those days it was the equivalent of the humanitarians because when - when I read about them or listen to anybody I think, eeh, shades of the Labour }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4265682\charrsid11536143 Church and}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143  the Socialist - Socialist Sunday School - yes, it was on a humanitarian principle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012655 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 After you left school and were working obviously your interests broadened out tremendously and you met a very much wider range of people.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14835199 AF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11012655 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6489771\charrsid11536143 Did you make any special friends - personal friends about that time?
