ouldn't do this and they wouldn't do that and I used to wonder at Mr Speke's patience - because he had the patience of Job - he never lost his temper and he would just say to them when they were - you know, going off, well, well, well, we'll have another 
t
alk when you feel a bit calmer, you see, or something like that. Well, I couldn't do that - I used to more or less hit out at them, you see, I had an Irish temper and have an Irish temper which I have to control, and - but I used to let them have the leng
